 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">If you want maximum affordability with real 1-on-1 human interaction, See Guru certified teachers and iTalki community tutors deliver the best value per dollar spent.</p>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4" id="how-to-get-the-most-from-cheap-1-on-1-lessons">How to Get the Most From Cheap 1-on-1 Lessons</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">A cheap lesson is only a good deal if you actually learn from it. Here is how to maximize every session:</p>
 <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-4 text-neutral-300 space-y-3">
 <li><strong>Prepare before your lesson.</strong> Write down 3-5 questions or topics you want to cover. Do not waste paid time figuring out what to say.</li>
 <li><strong>Ask for pronunciation feedback.</strong> Most learners improve fastest by focusing on sounds that do not exist in their native language.</li>
 <li><strong>Request correction.</strong> Tell your tutor to correct you immediately when you make mistakes. Gentle correction policies may slow your progress.</li>
 <li><strong>Record key vocabulary.</strong> Take notes during class and review them between sessions. This builds retention.</li>
 <li><strong>Book consistency over frequency.</strong> Two solid lessons per week beats four rushed ones. Quality contact time matters more than volume.</li>
 </ol>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4" id="what-to-look-for-in-a-budget-tutor">What to Look for in a Budget Tutor</h2>
 <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">Affordability matters, but the wrong tutor wastes money no matter how cheap the rate. Watch for these qualities:</p>
 <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-neutral-300 space-y-2">
 <li><strong>Ratings above 4.5 stars.</strong> Real student reviews reveal whether a tutor is reliable and helpful.</li>
 <li><strong>Teaching experience or qualifications.</strong> TEFL or CELTA certifications indicate structured training, not just fluency.</li>
 <li><strong>Specialization matching your goals.</strong> A conversation tutor may not be ideal for business English prep.</li>
 <li><strong>Availability that matches your schedule.</strong> A cheap tutor is frustrating if they are only available at odd hours.</li>
 <li><strong>Clear communication style.</strong> Some tutors talk too much. The best tutors ask questions and make you speak.</li>
 </ul>

 <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4" id="our-recommendation-start-with-see-guru">Our Recommendation: Start With See Guru</h2>
